Za a ba da izinin shiga Masallatai 50 a ranar Eid, babu sallar taro a Eidgah: Karnataka
Za a yi bikin Eid-ul-Azha, wanda aka fi sani da Bakrid, a ranar 31 ga Yuli da 1 ga Agusta.
Gwamnatin Karnataka ta ba da izinin yin sallar Eid-ul-Azha ne kawai a cikin masallatai da matsakaicin mutane 50 a lokaci guda kuma ta ce an hana yin sallar taro a Eidgah da sauran wurare saboda annobar coronavirus.
Masu zuwa masallatai don yin addu'a dole ne su sa abin rufe fuska kuma su kiyaye nesa ta zamantakewa, Sakataren Sashen Kula da 'Yan Kananan Mutane da Wakf AB Ibrahim ya ce a cikin umarni.
Ya ce kwamitin Hilal ya yanke shawarar cewa za a yi bikin Eid-ul-Azha, wanda aka fi sani da Bakrid, a ranar 31 ga Yuli a gundumar Udupi, Dakshina Kannada da Kodagu yayin da za a yi shi a ranar 1 ga Agusta a sauran jihohin.
Da yake lura cewa sallar taro na daya daga cikin muhimman al'adun da musulmai ke yi a lokacin Bakrid, umarnin ya ce saboda annobar COVID-19 an hana irin waɗannan abubuwan a Eidgah da sauran wurare.
Duk da haka, ana ba da izinin yin addu'a a cikin masallatai tare da iyakancewar cewa ba fiye da mutane 50 ba ne za su halarci.
Idan akwai mutane da yawa, ya kamata a yi addu'o'in a rukuni, in ji sashen a cikin umarnin.
Bai kamata a yi sallar Mass a wasu wurare kamar zauren taro, gine-ginen al'umma da kuma "Shadi Mahal" ba, umarnin ya kara da cewa.
Karnataka ta ba da izinin bude wuraren ibada da masallatai da sauran wuraren ibada ga masu ibada daga ranar 8 ga Yuni tare da duk matakan rigakafin COVID-19.
